@node DESCRIPTION "Relax · Description"
Description
===========
  Relax is a tool to control any of the 8-bit realy-cards around. It has
  a simple, but powerfull GUI for easy and fast handling. There are four
  different modes how the control can be done:

  1. Direct
  ---------
  In this mode all the acting is done directly. There are some buttons avail,
  like AllOn, AllOff, Invert, 1, 2, 3...

  2. Random
  ---------
  Here a random-generator decides which realys get switched. Useless realys
  can be switched off and the pause between the next step is setable.

  3. Step
  -------
  Two or more commands can be added to a list. The loopable list can be
  run with different times in pause. There can be unlimited entrys in a list.

  4. Time
  -------
  And here acting is done at defined times. Per step, a begin- and end-
  contition can be defined to various times. Also here there can be
  unlimited entrys in a list.

  All functions from the GUI are also avail via @{" ARexx " link AREXX}
@endnode

@node FEATURES "Relax · Features"
Features
========
  - Supports all 8-bit Realy-cards (2^n)
  - Realtime GUI
  - ARexx control
    - All GUI functions are avail
    - Fully transparent to GUI
    - Own process, so all actions can be aborted
  - 4 different modes of control
    - Direct
      - Direct control like on, off, 1, 2, 3
    - Random
      - Setable pause
      - Realys selectable
    - Step
      - Unlimited steps per list
      - Load and saveable step-lists
      - Variable pause per step
    - Time
      - Unlimited times per list
      - Load and saveable time-lists
  - Overall timerange from 10ms to 1 day
@endnode

@node REQUIREMENTS "Relax · Requirements"
Requirements
============
  - AmigaOS v3.x
  - Lamp.mcc (included)

  - Amiga Computer
  - 1mb RAM
  - 0.5mb HD

  - 8-bit Realy-card on the parallel-port

  @{" Tested hatdware " link HARDWARE}
@endnode

@node HARDWARE "Relax · Hardware"
Hardware
========
  Card                 From                  Port                State
  ----------------------------------------------------------------------
  RTA-1000             Conrad                parallel            @{b}Working@{ub}
@endnode

@node INSTALL "Relax · Installation"
Installation
============
  Installation is very simple.

  Just drag the Relax-drawer where you like.
  Relax doesn't need any assigns.
@endnode

@node USAGE "Relax · Usage"
Usage
=====
  Using Relax is very simple. The tool is designed so that every action can
  be aborted with no waiting. Also all gadgets can be used while the output
  process is running.

  @{i}Disable the 'Simulation'-checkmark in the main window if a real realy-
  card is connected, or nothing will happen.@{ui}

  @{b}Don't run the realy-card < 50ms pause for a longer time!@{ub}


  Menu/Settings
  -------------
  - You can enter 8 names/titels for the realys which becomes displayd in
      the 'Direct'- and 'Random'-window.
  - Select the output device, usualy PAR: or PRT:


  Direct
  ------
  - Direct & Random
    ---------------
    - Think this needs no explanation...

  - Step
    ----
    - Press 'Add' for a new entry. Set realy-contition and the pause
      afterwards, so before the next step begins.
    - @{i}Use can use drag&drop to bring the list-entrys in another order.@{ui}

  - Time
    ----
    - Pree 'Add' and set the begin- and end- realy-contition. Set begin-
      and end-time in H:M:S
    - Beware, there is no real checking of "the logic" in your list done,
      so pay attention here.

    - Press 'Load', 'Save' for in-export.
    - Press 'Run', 'Stop'

  ARexx
  -----
    - @{" ARexx " link AREXX}
@endnode

@node AREXX "Relax · ARexx"
ARexx
=====
  Relax contains a powerfull and easy to use Arexx-port. @{b}Please look at the
  included examples to get familiar with it.@{ub}

  ARexx port is 'RELAX.1'

  Command overview
  ----------------
  - Direct commands
    ---------------
    - SetASCII
    - GetASCII
    - SetOn
    - SetOff
    - IsOn
    - IsOff
    - SetAllOn
    - SetAllOff
    - IsAllOn
    - IsAllOff
    - Invert
    - InvertAll
  - Random commands
    ---------------
    - RunRandom
    - StopRandom
  - Step commands
    -------------
    - NewStepList
    - SetStepLoop
    - AddStep
    - RemoveStep
    - RunStepList
    - StopStepList
    - LoadStepList
    - SaveStepList
  - Direct commands
    ---------------
    - NewTimeList
    - AddTime
    - RemoveTime
    - RunTimeList
    - StopTimeList
    - LoadTimeList
    - SaveTimeList
  - Misc commands
    -------------
    - SetSimulation
    - IsSimulation
    - WaitSecs
    - WaitMics
    - SetGUI
    - ForceQuit


  Command explanation
  -------------------

  - Direct commands
    ---------------

    Func:   @{b}SetASCII@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set realys from a ascii-value. Valid values are 0-255.

    Func:   @{b}GetASCII@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: Decimal ASCII value
    Desc:   Get realys-status as ascii-value.

    Func:   @{b}SetOn@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set only the given realy to on. Valid numbers are 1-8.

    Func:   @{b}SetOff@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set only the given realy to off. Valid numbers are 1-8.

    Func:   @{b}IsOn@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: TRUE(1) if realy is on, else FALSE(0)
    Desc:   Check whether the given realy is on. Valid numbers are 1-8.

    Func:   @{b}IsOff@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: TRUE(1) if realy is off, else FALSE(0)
    Desc:   Check whether the given realy is off. Valid numbers are 1-8.

    Func:   @{b}SetAllOn@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set all realys to on.

    Func:   @{b}SetAllOff@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set all realys to off.

    Func:   @{b}IsAllOn@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: TRUE(1) if all realys are on, else FALSE(0)
    Desc:   Check whether all realys are on.

    Func:   @{b}IsAllOff@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: TRUE(1) if all realys are off, else FALSE(0)
    Desc:   Check whether all realys are off.

    Func:   @{b}Invert@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Invert only the given realy. Valid numbers are 1-8.

    Func:   @{b}InvertAll@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Invert all realys.


  - Random commands
    ---------------

    Func:   @{b}RunRamdom@{ub}
    Param:  RELAIS/A,WAIT_H/N,WAIT_M/N,WAIT_S/N,WAIT_MS/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Initializes and start the PRNG at the same time. The
            generator runs in a own process so the function immediately
            returns after start. You have to call 'StopRandom' to break
            the process. RELAIS/A is a mask and selects witch realys are
            involved. Ie. "XX......" means realy 1&2 can go on but all
            other should be always off. You _must_ use the character 'X'
            to set the mask-bit to 'on'. All other characters means 'off'.
            The other paramters select the waiting-time till the next cycle.
            TIME_H/N = hours (0-23), TIME_M/H = minutes (0-59), TIME_S =
            secounds (0-59), TIME_MS/N = milisecounds (10-999). The smallest
            pause are 10 milisecounds. No pause is invalid.

            ie: RunRandom "XX......" 0 0 0 100 (wait 100 msecs)
                RunRandom "....X.XX" 0 0 1 0   (wait 1 sec)

    Func:   @{b}StopRamdom@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Stop the PRNG process.

            ie: ...
                RunRandom "XX......" 0 0 0 500
                Wait 10
                StopRandom
                ...


  - Step commands
    -------------

    Func:   @{b}NewStepList@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Clear the current list off steps.

    Func:   @{b}SetStepLoop@{ub}
    Param:  STATUS/A
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set looping mode for the current steplist. Either 'ON'
            or 'OFF' in _upper_ case. If 'ON' and the process reach
            the last entry in the list it starts again from top.
            You can change this value while the process is running.

    Func:   AddStep@{ub}
    Param:  RELAIS/A,WAIT_H/N,WAIT_M/N,WAIT_S/N,WAIT_MS/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Add a single step to the current list. Same prinzip as
            'RunRandom'.

            ie: AddStep "X.X.X.X." 0 0 1 0
                AddStep ".X.X.X.X" 0 0 0 500

    Func:   @{b}RemoveStep@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Remove a single step from the current list. The parameter
            is the number of the entry in the list.

    Func:   @{b}RunStepList@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Start the step process. The list runs from top to buttom.
            If its empty, nothing will happen. Also here the function
            immediately return and you have to call 'StopStepList' to
            break to process.

            ie: ...
                SetStepLoop "ON"
                NewStepList
                AddStep "X.X.X.X." 0 0 1 0
                AddStep ".X.X.X.X" 0 0 0 500
                RunStepList
                Wait 10
                StopStepList

                NewStepList
                ...

    Func:   @{b}LoadStepList@{ub}
    Param:  NAME/A
    Return: TRUE(1) if ok, else FALSE(0) for an error
    Desc:   Load a step-list from disk. It also loads the step-loop switch.
            You must give the full path.

            ie: ...
                LoadStepList "ram:step_test"
                RunStepList
                Wait 10
                StopStepList
                ...

    Func:   @{b}SaveStepList@{ub}
    Param:  NAME/A
    Return: TRUE(1) if ok, else FALSE(0) for an error
    Desc:   Save the current step-list to disk. The step-loop switch also
            get saved. You must give the full path.

            ie: ...
                SetStepLoop "ON"
                NewStepList
                AddStep "X.X.X.X." 0 0 1 0
                AddStep ".X.X.X.X" 0 0 0 500
                SaveStepList "ram:step_test"
                ...


  - Time commands
    -------------

    Func:   @{b}NewTimeList@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Clear the current list off times.

    Func:   @{b}AddTime@{ub}
    Param:  RELAIS/A,WAIT_H/N,WAIT_M/N,WAIT_S/N,RELAIS/A,WAIT_H/N,WAIT_M/N,WAIT_S/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Add a single time to the current list. Same prinzip as
            'RunRandom', except that here is a start- and end-
            contition. Milisecounds are not avail and i think not needed
            here.

            ie: AddTime "X......." 22 0 0 "........" 22 1 0 (turn realy 1
                from 22:00:00 to 22:01:00 on)
            ie: AddTime "X......." 16 0 0 ".X......" 16 0 5 (turn realy 1
                from 16:00:00 to 16:00:05 on and _then_ turn realy 2 on)

    Func:   @{b}RemoveTime@{ub}
    Param:  NUMBER/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Remove a single time from the current list. The parameter
            is the number of the entry in the list.

    Func:   @{b}RunTimeList@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Start the time process. The process jumps directly to the entry
            in the list with overlaps with the current time. If its empty,
            nothing will happen. Also here the function immediately return
            and you have to call 'StopTimeList' to break to process.

            (coffee machine on realy 8 for 6:00 - 6:15)
            ie: ...
                NewTimeList
                AddTime ".......X" 6 0 0 "........" 6 15 0
                RunTimeList
                ...
                StopTimeList
                ...

    Func:   @{b}LoadTimeList@{ub}
    Param:  NAME/A
    Return: TRUE(1) if ok, else FALSE(0) for an error
    Desc:   Load a time-list from disk. You must give the full path.

            ie: ...
                LoadTimeList "ram:time_test"
                RunTimeList
                Wait 10
                StopStepList
                ...

    Func:   @{b}SaveTimeList@{ub}
    Param:  NAME/A
    Return: TRUE(1) if ok, else FALSE(0) for an error
    Desc:   Save the current step-list to disk. You must give the full path.

            ie: ...
                NewTimeList
                AddTime ".......X" 6 0 0 "........" 6 15 0
                SaveTimeList "ram:time_test"
                ...


  - Misc commands
    -------------

    Func:   @{b}SetSimulation@{ub}
    Param:  STATUS/A
    Return: None
    Desc:   Set simulation mode. Either 'ON' or 'OFF' in _upper_ case. If 'ON',
            no data is passes to the output, its simulated only. This switch
            must be on if no real card is connected. If 'OFF', data is passesd
            to output. If you disable the simulation while no real card is
            selected the application may frezze...

    Func:   @{b}IsSimulation@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: TRUE(1) if on, else FALSE(0)
    Desc:   Check whether simulation is currently turned on.

    Func:   @{b}WaitSecs@{ub}
    Param:  SECS/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Wait the given number of secounds. Same as REXX 'Wait'.

    Func:   @{b}WaitMics@{ub}
    Param:  MICS/N
    Return: None
    Desc:   Wait the given number of microsecounds. (not millisecounds!)

            ie: WaitMics 500000    /* half secound, 1 secs = 1000000 msecs */

    Func:   @{b}SetGUI@{ub}
    Param:  STATUS/A
    Return: None
    Desc:   Show or hide the GUI. Either 'ON' or 'OFF' in _upper_ case.
            All arexx-commands are directly reflect on the gui.

    Func:   @{b}ForceQuit@{ub}
    Param:  None
    Return: None
    Desc:   Forces programm quit.
@endnode

